  23 Aug 2005; Ian Leitch <port001@gentoo.org> aolserver-4.0.9-r1.ebuild,
  aolserver-4.0.10.ebuild:
  Allow enewuser to choose the correct shell, bug #103421

  27 Feb 2005; Ian Leitch <port001@gentoo.org> aolserver-4.0.10.ebuild:
  Install sample-config.tcl into /usr/share/doc instead of /usr/share/aolserver

  25 Feb 2005; Ian Leitch <port001@gentoo.org> aolserver-4.0.10.ebuild,
  -aolserver-4.0.8.ebuild, -aolserver-4.0.9.ebuild:
  Updated to use built_with_use. Removed old versions 4.0.8 and 4.0.9.

*aolserver-4.0.10 (27 Jan 2005)

  27 Jan 2005; Ian Leitch <port001@gentoo.org>
  +files/4.0.10/Makefile.global, +files/4.0.10/aolserver-4.0.10-nptl.patch,
  +files/4.0.10/aolserver.init, +files/4.0.10/config.tcl,
  +aolserver-4.0.10.ebuild:
  Version bump

*aolserver-4.0.9-r1 (05 Jan 2005)

  05 Jan 2005; Ian Leitch <port001@gentoo.org> +aolserver-4.0.9-r1.ebuild:
  Create missing /var/run/aolserver (fixes init script). Create group
  'aolserver' instead of 'web' and set aolserver user's shell to /bin/false.
  Also provided a pkg_setup() to correct these for users who are upgrading.

*aolserver-4.0.9 (05 Jan 2005)

  05 Jan 2005; Ian Leitch <port001@gentoo.org>
  -files/aolserver-4.0.8-nptl.patch,
  +files/4.0.8/aolserver-4.0.8-nptl.patch, +files/4.0.9/Makefile.global,
